The court decision postponing the imposition of sentence upon a convicted person or postponing the execution of a sentence that has been imposed, by the court. When the court suspends a sentence, it retain jurisdiction over the person, and may later set or execute a penalty. When a sentence is suspended the person is usually placed on probation. A violation of the conditions of probation may lead to revocation of probation and return to court for re-sentencing. 

Source: [VA Circuit Court Criminal Glossary](http://www.courts.state.va.us/courts/circuit/resources/manuals/cc_manual_criminal/glossary.pdf)